            Recently, ref. 
            30
             considered similar issues of noise learnability. They studied a different Pauli noise model with perfect initial state 





                      0



                \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\left|0\right\rangle$$\end{document}



            , perfect computational basis measurement, and noisy single qubit gates, and showed the existence of unlearnable information. In contrast, here we focus on the learnability of Pauli noise of multi-qubit Clifford gates assuming perfect single-qubit gates (with noisy SPAM), and in practice we make the standard assumption that noise on single-qubit gates is gate-independent (e.g.

              23

            ), in which case our noise learning results are interpreted as characterizing a dressed cycle.
